18/08/2009
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Tourists will be able to travel to Japan without visas starting on September 1st, the Foreign and Interior Ministry announced on Monday (August 17th). 
The Japanese Embassy in Bucharest announced that all Romanian citizens will be able to stay in Japan for up to 90 days without visas. 
This does not apply to Romanian citizens who intend to work in Japan. 
(Realitatea, Financiarul, Hotnews.ro - 17/08/09)
